    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 99.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch No. 60, of
                            the 17th instant, relative to the refusal of the French government to
                            permit Mr. Hammond, agent of the American Emigration Company at Havre,
                            to contract for the transport of emigrants through Havre to the United
                            States. You may ask for explanations from Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys, but you
                            will not make it a subject of protest or remonstrance without
                            instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
